== History ==
Although the exact date of establishment is unknown, it is伝えられている that in the past, fishermen from {{ill|Akita|ja|秋田|12=draft}} and {{ill|Tsugaru|ja|津軽|12=draft}} would travel here every spring for fishing and return in autumn. To escape dangers posed by the {{ill|Ainu|ja|アイヌ|12=draft}}, they built a small shrine enshrining the {{ill|Osema|ja|大麻|12=draft}} (talisman) from {{ill|Ise Jingū|ja|伊勢神宮|12=draft}} in {{ill|Karatsunai Town|ja|唐津内町|12=draft}}, calling it "Ise-dō." 

In the 10th year of {{ill|Tenshō|ja|天正|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)|lt=Tenshō Era|12=draft}} ({{ill|1582|ja|1582nd year|12=draft}}), the feudal lord {{ill|Kaisaki Norihiro|ja|蛎崎（松前）季広|12=draft}} relocated his seat to Kuramachi (present-day Fukuyama in Matsumae Town, 松前町字福山) and renamed the shrine as "Shinmei-sha" in reverence. In the first year of {{ill|Shōō|ja|承応|12=draft}} the lord of the {{ill|Matsumae Domain|ja|松前藩|12=draft}}, {{ill|Matsumae Takahiro|ja|松前高広|12=draft}}, built a new shrine building at the present location, relocating the shrine and officially receiving the sacred seal ({{ill|Shinji|ja|神璽|12=draft}}) from {{ill|Ise Jingū|ja|伊勢神宮|12=draft}}. In the 4th year of {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|12=draft}} in November, it was ranked as a mura-sha, and in December of the 8th year of Meiji the shrine was renamed "Tokuyama Daijingu," and in the following year (the 9th year of Meiji) it was promoted to a gōsha. In February of the 4th year of {{ill|Taishō|ja|大正|12=draft}} it was designated as a Shinzenheihaku-ryō Kōshin Shrine.

On March 5 of the 46th year of {{ill|Showa|ja|昭和|12=draft}}, the main shrine building was designated as a tangible cultural property of Hokkaido, and it was repaired in the 52nd year of Showa; concurrently, the worship hall was rebuilt in the Shinmei style, with completion tier 1]][[Category: in the following year (the 53rd year of Showa).

== Sub-shrines ==
Within the shrine precincts is a subsidiary shrine: Haguro Shrine (【associated with】 {{ill|Konohanasakuya-hime|ja|木花咲耶姫命|12=draft}}).

== Cultural Properties ==
* Main shrine building (designated by Hokkaido)
* Ridge plaque (designated by Hokkaido) (36 units)
* Torii (designated by Hokkaido)

