'''Tokuyama Daijingu''' (徳山大神宮) is a Shinto shrine located in {{ill|Hokkaido|ja|北海道|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Matsumae District|ja|松前郡|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Matsumae Town|ja|松前町|12=draft|12=draft}} at Shinmei 66. Its enshrined deities are {{ill|Amaterasu Ōmikami|ja|天照大御神|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Toyouke Ōmikami|ja|豊受大神|lt=Toyouke Ōmikami|1=Toyouke-hime|12=draft|12=draft}}, which are the primary deities, although an additional 46 deities are also enshrined (as described below). The former shrine ranking under the modern system was that of a Gōsha, and it is called the "Ichinomiya of Oshima" (渡島一宮).

== Worshipped deities (Saijin) ==
{{see also|{{ill|Saijin|ja|祭神|12=draft|12=draft}}}}
The primary enshrined deities are {{ill|Amaterasu Ōmikami|ja|天照大御神|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Toyouke Ōmikami|ja|豊受大神|lt=Toyouke Ōmikami|1=Toyouke-hime|12=draft|12=draft}}, and additionally 46 other deities are enshrined together (see below).

