'''Tokuyama Daijingu''' (徳山大神宮) is a Shinto shrine located in [[:en:Hokkaido|Hokkaido]], [[:en:Matsumae District, Hokkaido|Matsumae District]], {{ill|Matsumae Town|ja|松前町|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Matsumae Town|qq=|1=松前町|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q1307271}} at Shinmei 66. Its enshrined deities are {{ill|Amaterasu Ōmikami|ja|天照大御神|1=Amaterasu|lt=Amaterasu Ōmikami|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Amaterasu Ōmikami|13=User:Immanuelle/Amaterasu|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 天照大神}} and {{ill|Toyouke Ōmikami|ja|豊受大神|lt=Toyouke Ōmikami|1=Toyōke Ōmikami|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Toyouke Ōmikami|13=User:Immanuelle/Toyouke-hime|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to トヨウケビメ|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q2983724}}, which are the primary deities, although an additional 46 deities are also enshrined (as described below). The former shrine Ranking under the modern system was that of a Gōsha, and it is called the "Ichinomiya of Oshima" (渡島一宮).

== Worshipped deities (Saijin) ==
{{see also|{{ill|Saijin|ja|祭神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Saijin|qq=}}}}
The primary enshrined deities are {{ill|Amaterasu Ōmikami|ja|天照大御神|1=Amaterasu|lt=Amaterasu Ōmikami|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Amaterasu Ōmikami|13=User:Immanuelle/Amaterasu|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 天照大神}} and {{ill|Toyouke Ōmikami|ja|豊受大神|lt=Toyouke Ōmikami|1=Toyōke Ōmikami|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Toyouke Ōmikami|13=User:Immanuelle/Toyouke-hime|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to トヨウケビメ|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q2983724}}, and additionally 46 other deities are enshrined together (see below).

== History ==
Although the exact date of establishment is unknown, it is伝えられている that in the past, fishermen from {{ill|Akita|ja|秋田|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Akita|qq=|1=Akita|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11256953}} and {{ill|Tsugaru|ja|津軽|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsugaru|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 津軽地方|1=Tsugaru region|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11556401}} would travel here every spring for fishing and return in autumn. To escape dangers posed by the [[:en:Ainu people|Ainu]], they built a small shrine enshrining the [[:en:Cannabis (drug)|Osema]] (talisman) from [[:en:Ise Shrine|Ise Jingū]] in {{ill|Karatsunai Town|ja|唐津内町|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Karatsunai Town|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, calling it "Ise-dō." 

In the 10th year of [[:en:Tenshō (Momoyama period)|Tenshō Era]] ([[:en:1582|1582]]), the feudal lord {{ill|Kaisaki Norihiro|ja|蛎崎（松前）季広|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kaisaki Norihiro|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} relocated his seat to Kuramachi (present-day Fukuyama in Matsumae Town, 松前町字福山) and renamed the shrine as "Shinmei-sha" in reverence. In the first year of [[:en:Jōō (Edo period)|Shōō]] the lord of the [[:en:Matsumae Domain|Matsumae Domain]], {{ill|Matsumae Takahiro|ja|松前高広|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Matsumae Takahiro|qq=|1=Matsumae Takahiro|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q8514302}}, built a new shrine building at the present location, relocating the shrine and officially receiving the sacred seal ({{ill|Shinji|ja|神璽|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinji|qq=|1=Shenxi|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q5371535}}) from [[:en:Ise Shrine|Ise Jingū]]. In the 4th year of [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] in November, it was Ranked as a mura-sha, and in December of the 8th year of Meiji the shrine was renamed "Tokuyama Daijingu," and in the following year (the 9th year of Meiji) it was promoted to a gōsha. In February of the 4th year of [[:en:Taishō era|Taishō]] it was designated as a Shinzenheihaku-ryō Kōshin Shrine.

On March 5 of the 46th year of [[:en:Shōwa era|Showa]], the main shrine building was designated as a tangible cultural property of Hokkaido, and it was repaired in the 52nd year of Showa; concurrently, the worship hall was rebuilt in the Shinmei style, with Completion tier 1]][[Category: in the following year (the 53rd year of Showa).

== Sub-shrines ==
Within the shrine precincts is a subsidiary shrine: Haguro Shrine (【associated with】 {{ill|Konohanasakuya-hime|ja|木花咲耶姫命|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Konohanasakuya-hime|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to コノハナノサクヤビメ}}).

== Cultural Properties ==
* Main shrine building (designated by Hokkaido)
* Ridge plaque (designated by Hokkaido) (36 units)
* Torii (designated by Hokkaido)

